cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on learning about physical object motion through video prediction. Additionally, the paper introduces a dataset of robot interactions involving pushing motions, which suggests a robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of unsupervised learning also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper's focus on predicting how actions affect objects in the environment suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper's exploration of video prediction for real-world interactive agents suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
